      Toggle Spectrum Plots
      *EVT* *evt* 
      menu
      xpaset -p $xpa_method tcl toggle_spectrum_shape
      
      Toggle GLVary Plots
      *EVT* *evt* 
      menu
      xpaset -p $xpa_method tcl toggle_glvary_shape

      ---
      
      help
      
        These tasks will enable interactive functionality for the
        currently **selected** regions.  These tasks operate on
        files on disk, so things like smoothing do not affect the results.
      
        The tasks are described below:
        
        Counts - display the sum of the pixel values in the text box above
            the selected region. 
        
        Elastic Ellipse - This task only works with ellipse and box shapes. 
            When activated, the shape changes color to violet. After the
            shape is moved, edited, or rotated, the shape will resize,
            reorient, and recenter itself to match the image moments of the 
            data inside the shape. When disabled the color of the shape will
            change to green.
            
        Lightcurve - As the region is moved, a plot of the lightcurve 
            (count rate vs time) is updated. By default the spectrum is
            creates with 1000second bins. This value can be changed 
            by changing the "lc_binsize" in dax.par

                    pset dax lc_binzie=100
            
        Spectrum - As the region is moved, a plot of the spectrum 
            (channel vs. counts). By default the spectrum is grouped to  
            have 1 count per group. This can be changed by changing
            the 'grptype' 'grpval' 'grpbin' in dax.par
            These parameters are the same as grptype, grptypeval, 
            and binspec in the dmgroup tool.
            
                    pset dax grptype=NONE

        GLVary - As the region is moved, the GLVary Bayesian blocks
            lightcurve is plotted. 
            
        
      endhelp

  endhmenu

